[SN]TITLE[SN]
Joe Cordina: Welsh boxer beats Jose Aguilar on pro boxing debut

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Joe Cordina marked his professional debut with a fourth-round stoppage win over Jose Aguilar in Liverpool.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Welsh Commonwealth Games bronze medallist dominated the super featherweight contest from the start.
The 25-year-old is now set to face Liverpool's Jay Carney on the Anthony Joshua's v Wladimir Klitschko bill at Wembley Stadium on 29 April.
Cordina won a bronze for Wales in Glasgow 2014 and is a former European amateur champion.
